summary: What I like about Little My in this Moominvalley iteration is that she is absolutely a Bastard Gremlin, but she never dances...
body:
What I like about Little My in this Moominvalley iteration is that she is absolutely a Bastard Gremlin, but she never dances around an issue. And sometimes, she’s the voice of reason in a situation where folks are afraid of speaking up, or stuck with their head in the clouds. If Moomin isn’t sticking up for himself in certain situations, Little My makes damn sure that he does.

Of course, she will take any opportunity to make chaos in the meantime.

summary: In Moomin, children who are abused turn invisible. Ninny was abused by her former caretaker so much she lost her voice and faded...
caption:
In Moomin, children who are abused turn invisible. Ninny was abused by her former caretaker so much she lost her voice and faded away, so the Moomins take her in and slowly help her heal and regain her confidence through love and compassion. Tove Jansson wrote “Thank you for making me visible again” in Tuulikki Pietilä’s, her wife, copy of the novel

This story will be getting adapted in Moominvalley 2019 as well
